    "Here, we start with the central band subspace of the BM model in the absence of any substrate potential, and then project the spatiallyvarying sublattice potential ∆(r) into this subspace.",
    "Numerically it can be shown that the overlap between the fixed Hilbert space and the Hilbert space for a given constant sublattice potential ∆ 0 is very high in the range ∆ 0 ≲ 30meV, justifying this approach [65].",
    "The substrate potential operator takes the form∆(r) = ∆ 1 (r)σ z 0 0 ∆ 2 (r)σ z,(119)where ∆ l (r) is the substrate potential on layer l. We typically consider cases where only one of the layers is aligned with the hBN, i.e.",
    "∆ 1 (r) = ∆(r), ∆ 2 (r) = 0.",
    "We project this sublattice potential directly onto the central bands |ψ τ a (k)⟩ evaluated at ∆ = 0, i.e.⟨ψ τ a (k)| ∆ |ψ τ ′ a ′ (k ′)⟩ = δ τ,τ ′ δ k2,k ′ 2 ∆ k1a;k ′ 1 a ′ (k 2, τ),(120)where we assumed that the substrate potential is only a function of x 1."
